<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-215-644  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 215 644.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  March 8 1990 n1380* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Instem continues recovery, warmed against recession by #12.5morder book. (Instem Group PLC)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Instem Group PLC (finance).andO;Topic:     Financial StabilityRecoveryStrategic PlanningOrders.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>INSTEM CONTINUES RECOVERY, WARMED AGAINST RECESSIONandM;BY #12.5m ORDER BOOKandM;Instem Group Plc has built on the strong recovery staged in 1988 over thepast 12 months and prospects for the current year look decidedly rosy with anorder book of #12.5m, up from #8.5m a year ago.andP;  Instem reckons that theperformance for 1989 (see Company Results) was the best in its 20-yearhistory.andP;  The Stafford company has established a new management structurethat sees the creation of two major divisions - the Instem Electronics armthat takes in its contract manufacture, and the Instem Computer Systems arm,which takes in the other four niche market activities - systems for use inpower generation, water management, industrial processing and scientificresearch.andP;  And, emulating what has proved a very successful model for RacalElectronics Plc, the company has created a central services group, inInstem's case comprising finance, marketing, quality assurance and personnel.andO;&quot;Whist we see recessionary forces in evidence, with the consequent pressureon margins,&quot; concludes Instem chairman David Gare, &quot;I look forward tocontinuing the momentum developed over the past two years.&quot;andO;</TEXT></DOC>